    "Section 4 is dedicated to displaying AI-enhanced metasurface systems from imaging to innovative functions, which show AI's powerful ability to extract physics information.",
    "Finally, we make a conclusion and outlook by exploring the limits and challenges of AI for metasurface in Section 5.",
    "Basic concepts 2.1 MetasurfaceThe advantage of metasurfaces over traditional optical devices lies in their ability to control electromagnetic waves' phase through subwavelength-thick nanoantennas on the surface of the medium.",
    "Phase modulation enables the independent control of amplitude, phase, and polarization state.",
    "The primary forward modulation method for metasurfaces is phase modulation, which includes three phase design approaches: resonant phase, propagating phase, and geometric phase (PB-phase).The general design of metasurfaces can be categorized into forward design, inverse design, and end-to-end design."
